```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by=['year'])
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['wheat'], color='green')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.title('What is the trend in wheat production over time?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['wheat'], data['wages'])

    plt.ylabel('Wages')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wheat production and wages?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    plt.boxplot(data['wages'], positions=data['year'], widths=5, showfliers=True, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), medianprops=dict(color='black'), whiskerprops=dict(color='black'), capprops=dict(color='black'))
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wages')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wages over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.bar(data['year'], data['wheat'], color='green')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Wheat Production')
    plt.title('What is the average wheat production per year?')
    plt.axhline(y=data['wheat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Wheat Production')
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['wheat'], bins=10, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['wheat'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['wheat'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wheat production?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
